    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"350\" confluence-query-params=\"effects=drop-shadow\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540613/rfm_mayaFileNode.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431559326&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;effects=drop-shadow&amp;width=350&amp;height=658\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544540613/rfm_mayaFileNode.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431559326&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544540631\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfm_mayaFileNode.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544540613\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"5c21e8c5-a90e-4cd3-a759-63dc1486684a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540613/rfm_mayaFileNode.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431559326&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;effects=drop-shadow&amp;width=482&amp;height=907 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540613/rfm_mayaFileNode.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431559326&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;effects=drop-shadow&amp;width=350&amp;height=658 1x\"></span></p><p>The Maya file node provides a convenient way to apply textures to surfaces and drive parameters. However, RenderMan only supports a subset of the controls based on the preferred workflow.</p><p> </p><h3 id=\"MayaFileNode-SupportedFeatures:\">Supported Features:</h3><h4 id=\"MayaFileNode-FileAttributes\">File Attributes</h4><p><strong>Image Name</strong> - The path to the texture(s) you want to use</p><p><strong>UV Tiling Mode</strong> - We support all except for Explicit Tiles</p><p><strong>Use Image Sequence</strong> - This can be more convenient than using expressions in other nodes</p><p> </p><h4 id=\"MayaFileNode-ColorBalance\">Color Balance</h4><p><strong>Default Color</strong> - This color fills-in where there is no texture coverage</p><p><strong>Color Gain</strong> - This is a color multiplier for the texture</p><p><strong>Color Offset</strong> - Adds this color value to the texture</p><p><strong>Alpha Gain</strong> - A multiplier for the texture alpha value (your texture needs an alpha channel unless you have selected Alpha is Luminance)</p><p><strong>Alpha Offset</strong> - Adds this value to the alpha value of the texture (your texture needs an alpha channel unless you have selected Alpha is Luminance)</p><p> </p><h4 id=\"MayaFileNode-Effects\">Effects</h4><p><strong>Invert</strong> - Inverts the values of the texture, colors become their opposite value on the color wheel</p><p><strong>Color Remap</strong> - Use a ramp to change hue and contrast values</p><p> </p><h3 id=\"MayaFileNode-RenderManControls:\">RenderMan Controls: </h3><p>We use our own file filtering options contained in the RenderMan rollout. We recommend Box and it is the default.</p><p> </p><p> </p>"
    }
  },
